The Nigerian Export Processing Zones Authority (NEPZA) and the Abuja Chamber of Commerce and Industry (ACCI) have thrown their weights behind a policy on operations for blockchain businesses in the country. In a press statement yesterday, the managing director of NEPZA, Prof Adesoji Adesugba, stated that the authority was considering the launch of a policy in consultation with other relevant agencies on the opening up of Nigeriaâ€™s free zones to blockchain tech and crypto currency operations. Prof Adesugba, while speaking with two blockchain firms during a visit to his office, noted that Nigeria was missing out in revenue from the sector. On its part, ACCI stated that it would support a roundtable on ways the multi-trillion dollar crypto currency and block chain tech policy could be developed in the country. Faruk Shauibu